@startuml
' @id(SEQ-RENDER-DIAGRAM-PAGE)
' @ref(USE-VIEW-DIAGRAMS)
' Objective-side flow: system fonts are loaded into the usvg font
' database BEFORE any SVG is parsed, so <text> glyphs are rasterized.
title Render a diagram page to the canvas (objective)

actor "Developer" as Dev
participant "MddViewer\n(eframe::App)" as Viewer
database ".mdd/rendered/*.svg" as FS
participant "FontDatabase\n(usvg fontdb)" as FontDb
participant "usvg::Tree" as Usvg
participant "resvg + tiny-skia" as Resvg
participant "egui painter" as Painter

Dev -> Viewer : open / select diagram file
Viewer -> FontDb : load_system_fonts() (once, cached)
note right of FontDb
  Objective: the font database is populated
  with the host's system fonts before the
  first parse. usvg::Options.font_family is
  set to a sane default. See OCL-FONTDB-POPULATED
  and DOM-FONT-DATABASE.
end note
FontDb --> Viewer : fontCount > 0

Viewer -> FS : read(.mdd/rendered/<page>.svg)
FS --> Viewer : svg_bytes
Viewer -> Usvg : parse_intrinsic_size(bytes, opts WITH fontdb)
Usvg --> Viewer : intrinsic size

loop each painted frame (zoom changed)
  Viewer -> Usvg : Tree::from_data(bytes, opts WITH fontdb)
  Viewer -> Resvg : render(tree, scale) -> Pixmap
  Resvg --> Viewer : premultiplied RGBA (glyphs included)
  Viewer -> Viewer : demultiply_rgba()
  Viewer -> Painter : load_texture() + painter.image()
  Painter --> Dev : diagram drawn WITH text
end
@enduml
